<p style="font-size: 24px; line-height: 28px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 20px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #e45206; font-weight: bold;">I&rsquo;m Getting Bombarded with Solar Offers &mdash; How Do I Choose?</p>
<p style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 22px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 5px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #666666;">About 10 years ago, solar installers numbered in the hundreds. Today, there are <a style="text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold; color: #61af3f;" href="http://www.seia.org/research-resources/solar-industry-data">nearly 180,000</a> solar professionals employed across more than 6,000 businesses&mdash;just in the United States alone.</p>
<p style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 22px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 15px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #666666;">And as a homeowner, you probably feel like you&rsquo;re receiving solicitations from every single one. New offers via email, post, and phone continue to flood into your life, causing you to feel overwhelmed by the sheer volume of choices.</p>
<p style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 22px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 15px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #666666;">So how do you select the right photovoltaic (PV) installer for your needs? We&rsquo;ve written a free step-by-step guide to help you transform a sea of candidates into a much more manageable pool of options.</p>
