<div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; color: #f6f6f6; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">
<table align="center" bgcolor="#F6F6F6" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="634">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;" height="146" width="159">
<div style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-right: 15px;"><img src="http://pages.directenergysolar.com/rs/410-XAV-850/images/Newsletter_TipofMonthIcon.jpg" alt="Energy Efficiency Tip of the Month" height="169" border="0" width="158" /></div>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;" width="475">
<div style="margin-top: 23px; margin-bottom: 0px;">
<p style="color: #1c3f94; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 22px; margin-bottom: 15px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-right: 20px; text-align: left;">Lower the average temperature of your HVAC and water systems. It&rsquo;s easy to do, and a few degrees isn&rsquo;t a noticeable change&mdash;try it out yourself!</p>
<p style="color: #666666; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 22px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-top: 0px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 10px; text-align: left;">The more energy efficient you become, the less electricity you use. Reduced power consumption means you&rsquo;ll need fewer solar panels to cover all of your electricity requirements! So, energy efficiency not only offers instant utility bill savings but also indirect savings if you decide to go solar.</p>
</div>
